Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "pripazi" in different forms and positions:

1. *Pripazi* na korake dok hodaš po ledu. (Be careful of your steps while walking on ice.)
2. *Pripazite* da ne izgubite ključeve. (Be careful not to lose your keys.)
3. Molim te, *pripazi* na decu dok ja obavim kupovinu. (Please watch the kids while I do the shopping.)
4. *Pripazio* je na svaku sitnicu i zato je sve prošlo bez problema. (He paid attention to every detail and that's why everything went smoothly.)
5. Kada voziš automobil, uvek moraš *pripaziti* na saobraćajne znakove. (When you're driving a car, you always have to pay attention to traffic signs.)
6. *Pripazite* da ne oštetite nameštaj prilikom selidbe. (Be careful not to damage the furniture during the move.)
7. Iako je bio umoran, *pripazio* je na svoje obaveze. (Even though he was tired, he paid attention to his duties.)
8. Učitelj je rekao učenicima da *pripaze* na gramatičke greške u svom pismu. (The teacher told the students to watch out for grammatical errors in their essay.)

I hope these examples help! Let me know if you have any other questions.